<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n38206d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38206d">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38206d"> 206(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> J&aacute;n bin J&aacute;n = F. Adam / Ibl&iacute;s = Satan ~~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">And what easier than to islamise the old Zoroasterism, to transform Ahrim&aacute;n into <mark>Ibl&iacute;s the Shayt&aacute;n</mark>, <mark>J&aacute;n bin J&aacute;n into Father Adam</mark>, and the Divs and Peris of Kayomars and the olden Guebre Kings into the Jinns and Jinniyahs of Sulayman? <small> Richard F. Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo;, <a name="RBTE1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE1"><cite title="source">The Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) X, 77</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
